@Node "Add" "RxMUI Functions - Add"

  @{b}Add@{ub} - Adds an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = Add(parent,child,before)
    <parent/V>,<child/V>,[pred/V]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Adds @{i}child@{ui} to @{i}parent@{ui}.

    The rules are:

    1. @{i}child@{ui} bust be free
    2. @{i}parent@{ui} and @{i}child@{ui} must be compatible

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    parent - the object to add @{i}child@{ui} to
    child - the object to add to @{i}parent@{ui}
    pred - add @{i}child@{ui} after this (only for Menu and Menuitem)

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}

    [NO_MEM] not enough resources to complete the operation
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}parent@{ui} or @{i}child@{ui} not found
    [BUSY_OBJ] @{i}child@{ui} is busy

  @{b}See@{ub}
    @{"Remove()" LINK "Remove"}

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    call DoMethod("group","InitChange")
    call Remove("old_obj")
    call Add("group","new_obj")
    call DoMethod("group","ExitChange")

@EndNode

@Node "AppMessage" "RxMUI Functions - AppMessage"

  @{b}AppMessage@{ub} - Instructs RxMUI to receive APPEVENT.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = AppMessage(obj)
    <obj/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Tells RxMUI you want to receive APPEVENT when an icon is
    dropped into @{i}obj@{ui}.

    The rules are:

    1. @{i}obj@{ui} can be any kind of object not only a window
    2. @{i}obj@{ui} must be in a window linked to an application

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object you want to receive APPEVENT from

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_MEM] not enough resources to complete the operation
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Object handling" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectsHandling"}

@EndNode

@Node "AppPushId" "RxMUI Functions - AppPushId"

  @{b}AppPushId@{ub} - Returns an export key.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = AppPushID(app)
    <app/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    This function returns a key ID to be used with PushMethod().

    You pass it the name of an Application object and it will
    return a key string ID that can be exported to another ARexx
    macros and used with PushMethod().

    The result is NOT of your interest: the only thing you can do
    is to match it with Null() to see if the function failed (may
    fail iff its argument is not an application).

    This is the mechanism used to control a RxMUI object outside
    the macro where it was created (remember that MUI in itself
    is monotask oriented and RxMUI is supposed to be SAFE):

     o in macro A:
       o create your application
       o obtain a key with this function.
       o launch the other macro B and pass it the key

     o in macro B
       o use PushMethod() with the key as first argument

    Any time PushMethod() is used in B , the macro B is suspended
    until the method reaches its goal. This makes the all thing
    very safe.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    app - the application to export

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    key - a key or Null() for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}app@{ui} not found or it is not an application object

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    let's suppose you created an application object and a text
    object named "info":

    o in macro A:
      key = AppPushID("app")
      address command "run >nil: <nil: B" c2x(key)
    o in macro B:
      parse arg id
      id = x2c(id)
      call PushMethod(id,"info","set","contents","Ok, I started")

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"PushMethod()" LINK "PushMethod"}

@EndNode

@Node "DandD" "RxMUI Functions - DandD"

  @{b}DandD@{ub} - Instructs RxMUI to be prepared for drag and drop.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = DandD(from,to,flags)
    <from/V>,<to/V>,[options]

  @{b}Function@{ub}

    Tells RxMUI to install a drag and drop mechanism from @{i}from@{ui} to
    @{i}to@{ui}

    options is one or more of:

    o AUTO - drag & drop is performed internally by RxMUI itself,
      between:

      o list <-> list
      o list <-> string
      o list -> text
      o string <-> string
      o string -> text

    o BOTH - the d&d is also from @{i}to@{ui} to @{i}from@{ui}

    o NOSELF - forbid an object (e.g. a List) to perform drag and
      drop within itself; the other flags are ignored, so d&d
      must be handled manually

    o REMOVE - remove dragged entries from a Listview

    o SORTED - insert entries sorted in a Listview

    If you don't specify AUTO, drag and drop must be handled by
    yourself in the macro. Look at the examples.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    from - the drag start from this object
    to - the drop goes to this object
    options - see above

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_MEM] not enough resources to complete the operation
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}from@{ui} or @{i}to@{ui} not found
    [BAD_DANDD] objects are not compatible for an AUTO D&D operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Object handling" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectsHandling"}

@EndNode

@Node "Dispose" "RxMUI Functions - Dispose"

  @{b}Dispose@{ub} - Disposes an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = Dispose(obj)
    <obj/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Disposes an object.

    The rules are:

    1. The object can refuse to be disposed
    2. The object is first removed and then disposed
    3. Any notification to the object is killed

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to dispose

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [BUSY_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} is busy

@EndNode

@Node "DoMethod" "RxMUI Functions - DoMethod"

  @{b}DoMethod@{ub} - Invokes a method.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = DoMethod(obj,method,parms)
    <obj/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Invokes a method on an object.

    Any class defines the rules for its own methods.

    Note that the var RC will contain the real result from the
    method. It may be useful in some situation.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to invoke method on
    method - a valid and direct method for @{i}obj@{ui}
    parms - parameters for @{i}method@{ui}

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [NO_METHOD] @{i}method@{ui} is not valid for @{i}obj@{ui}
    [METHOD_NOTIFYONLY] @{i}method@{ui} may only be used in notifications

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"CoerceMethod()" LINK "CoerceMethod"} @{"Methods" LINK "RxMUI.guide/Methods"}

@EndNode

@Node "CoerceMethod" "RxMUI Functions - CoerceMethod"

  @{b}CoerceMethod@{ub} - Invokes a foreign method.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = CoerceMethod(classObj,obj,method,parms)
    <classObj/V>,<obj/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Invokes the method @{i}method@{ui} of the class of @{i}classObj@{ui} on @{i}obj@{ui}.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    classObj - @{i}method@{ui} is a method of the class of this object
    obj - the object to invoke @{i}method@{ui} on
    method - a valid and direct method for @{i}classObj@{ui}
    parms - parameters for @{i}method@{ui}

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} or @{i}classObj@{ui} not found
    [NO_METHOD] @{i}method@{ui} is not valid for @{i}classObj@{ui}
    [METHOD_NOTIFYONLY] @{i}method@{ui} may only be used in notifications

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"DoMethod()" LINK "DoMethod"} @{"Methods" LINK "RxMUI.guide/Methods"}

@EndNode

@Node "PushMethod" "RxMUI Functions - PushMethod"

  @{b}PushMethod@{ub} - Invokes a method on a foreign object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = PushMethod(keyID,obj,method,parms)
    <keyID>,<obj/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Invokes a method on a object outside the macro where it was
    created.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    key - the key return by AppPushID()
    obj - the object to invoke method on
    method - a valid and direct method for @{i}obj@{ui}
    parms - parameters for @{i}method@{ui}

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [NO_METHOD] @{i}method@{ui} is not valid for @{i}obj@{ui}
    [METHOD_NOTIFYONLY] @{i}method@{ui} may only be used in notifications

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"AppPushID()" LINK "AppPushId"}

@EndNode

@Node "GetAttr" "RxMUI Functions - GetAttr"

  @{b}GetAttr@{ub} - Reads an attribute.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = GetAttr(obj,attr,var)
    <obj/V>,<attr/V>,<var/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Reads the value of an attribute of an object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to read the attribute of
    attr - the attribute to read
    var - an ARexx var name where the value of @{i}attr@{ui} will be
          written

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [ATTR_IS_NOT_G] the attribute can't be read
    [BAD_SET_GET] the operation failed for some reason

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    call GetAttr("string","contents","c")
    say c

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MultiGetAttr()" LINK MultiGetAttr} @{"xget()" LINK xget}

@EndNode

@Node "xget" "RxMUI Functions - xget"

  @{b}xget@{ub} - Reads an attribute.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    value = xget(obj,attr)
    <obj/V>,<attr/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Reads an attribute of an object and returns its value.

    Warning: if the type of the attribute is String, the result
    is truncated to the first null char found.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to read the attribute of
    attr - the attribute to read

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    value - the value of the attribute

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    say xget("string","contents")

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MultiGetAttr()" LINK "MultiGetAttr"} @{"GetAttr()" LINK "GetAttr"}

@EndNode

@Node "Handle" "RxMUI Functions - Handle"

  @{b}Handle@{ub} - Handles an Application object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = Handle(app,stem,signals)
    <app/V>,<stem/V>,[signals/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Please, use this function sparely, because it uses many cpu
    time. Usually, you should use NewHandle(), except when there
    is a very hard need to wait for signals in the macro itself.
    I never had such a need.

    Handles the object @{i}app@{ui} of class Application.

    Handling of applications in RxMUI is done via this function.

    The standard cycle to do that is:

    ctrl_c=2**12
    s=0
    do forever
        call handle("APP","H",s)
        do i=0 to h.num-1
            if h.i="QUIT" then exit
            if h.i==... then
            ...
        end
        s=Wait(or(h.signals,ctrl_c))
        if and(s,ctrl_c)~=0 then exit
    end

    Handle() writes in @{i}stem@{ui}.num the number of the entries to be
    parsed and in @{i}stem@{ui}.i i=0,...,@{i}stem@{ui}.num-1 the name of the
    object.

    When @{i}stem@{ui}.i is QUIT the application wants to exit and the
    user should exit from the macro or dispose the application.

    Otherwise @{i}stem@{ui}.i is the name of an object that notified the
    application via a

    res = Notify(obj,attr,value,"APP","RETURNID")

    The cycle is very critical: if you do time consuming
    operation (ARexx is slow !!!) you should invoke the method
    INPUTBUFFERED on the application as in:

    ctrl_c=2**12
    s=0
    do forever
        call handle("APP","H",s)
        do i=0 to h.num-1
            if h.i="QUIT" then exit
            if h.i=="GO" then
                do i=0 to 1000
                    say i
                    call DoMethod("APP","INPUTBUFFERED")
                end
            end
        end
        s=Wait(or(h.signals,ctrl_c))
        if and(s,ctrl_c)~=0 then exit
    end

    If you need to wait for other signals (e.g. for messages on a
    port) you can pass them to the rmh.library/Wait() function.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    app - the application to handle
    stem - an ARexx stem name the function will fill
    signals - signal received by wait()

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}app@{ui} not found or it is not an application object

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"NewHandle()" LINK "NewHandle"} @{"Object handling" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectsHandling"}

@EndNode

@Node "NewHandle" "RxMUI Functions - NewHandle"

  @{b}NewHandle@{ub} - Handles an Application object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = NewHandle(app,stem,signals)
    <app/V>,<stem/V>,[signals/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Handles the object @{i}app@{ui} of class Application.

    Handling of applications in RxMUI is done via this function.

    The standard cycle to do that is:

    ctrl_c=2**12
    do forever
        call NewHandle("APP","H",ctrl_c)
        if and(h.signals,ctrl_c)>0 then exit
        if h.EventFlag then
            select
                when h.event="QUIT" then exit
                when h.event==... then
                ...
            end
    end

    As you can see the difference with Handle() is that
    NewHandle() always returns just one event and waits
    internally for the signals.

    You should use Handle() only in the case you really have to
    wait for the signals in your code (e.g. you have to call
    rxsocket.library/WaitSelect() to wait for sockets events).

    NewHandle() reads from @{i}stem@{ui}:

    o .NoWait - a boolean which indicates if the function should
      wait for signals or not. Default is 0.

    NewHandle() writes in @{i}stem@{ui}:

    o .EventFlag - a boolean which indicates that there is an
      event to be dispatched

    o .Event - the name of the event that triggered a
      notification to the application.

    o .Signals - the signals received

    When @{i}stem@{ui}.event is QUIT the application wants to exit and the
    user should exit from the macro or dispose the application.

    Otherwise @{i}stem@{ui}.event is the name of an object that notified
    the application via a

    res = Notify(obj,attr,value,"APP","RETURNID")

    If you need to wait for other signals (e.g. for messages on a
    port) you can pass them in @{i}signals@{ui}.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    app - the Application object to handle
    stem - stem name the function will fill
    signals - user signals to wait for

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Handle()" LINK "Handle"} @{"Object handling" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectsHandling"}

@EndNode

@Node "Notify" "RxMUI Functions - Notify"

  @{b}Notify@{ub} - Adds a notification.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = Notify(notifier,attr,value,target,method,parms)
    <notifier/V>,<attr/V>,<value/V>,<target/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Adds a notification from @{i}notifier@{ui} to @{i}target@{ui} triggered by @{i}attr@{ui}
    when it changes to @{i}value@{ui} invoking @{i}method@{ui} on @{i}target@{ui} with
    @{i}parms@{ui}.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    notifier - the object that notifies
    attr - the attribute that triggers the notification
    value - the value of @{i}attr@{ui} that causes the notification
    target - the target of the notification. Specials values are:
       o _app - the application notifier belongs to
       o _win - the window notifier belongs to
       o _self - @{i}notifier@{ui} itself
       o method - a valid an indirect method to invoke on @{i}target@{ui}
       o parms - parameters for @{i}method@{ui}

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}notifier@{ui} or @{i}target@{ui} not found
    [NO_METHOD] @{i}method@{ui} is not valid for @{i}target@{ui}
    [METHOD_NONOTIFY] @{i}method@{ui} is direct-only
    [BAD_NOTIFY] the notification can't be added for some reason

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Notification" LINK "RxMUI.guide/Notification"}

@EndNode

@Node "Help" "RxMUI Functions - Help"

  @{b}Help@{ub} - Returns RxMUI functions help strings.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    string = help(fun)
    <fun>

  @{b}Function@{ub}

    Returns the help string associated with the function @{i}fun@{ui}.

    The same string can be obtained with rxhelp.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    fun - a RxMUI function name

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    string - the help string for @{i}fun@{ui}

@EndNode

@Node "KillNotify" "RxMUI Functions - KillNotify"

  @{b}KillNotify@{ub} - Kills notifications.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = KillNotify(from,to)
    <from/V>,<to/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Kills any notification from @{i}from@{ui} to @{i}to@{ui}.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    from - the notifier
    to - the notified

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}from@{ui} or @{i}to@{ui} not found

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Notification" LINK "RxMUI.guide/Notification"}

@EndNode

@Node "NewObj" "RxMUI Functions - NewObj"

  @{b}NewObj@{ub} - Creates an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = NewObj(className,objName,stem,freeChild)
    <class/V>,[name/O],[stem/V],[freeChild/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}

    Create an object of class @{i}class@{ui} named @{i}name@{ui} reading its
    attributes from @{i}stem@{ui}, if present, or @{i}name@{ui}.

    @{i}freeChild@{ui} makes NewObj() destroy all the internal buffers and
    resets child stems.

    Note that during object creation, all the objects defined in
    @{i}name@{ui} itself or @{i}stem@{ui}, if supplied, are created.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    class - the class the object is istance of
    name - the name of the object
    stem - Init attribute are here, if present
    freeChild - reset children - default 1

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_MEM] not enough mem to complete the operation
    [BAD_VALUE] some Init attributes was set to a bad value
    [BAD_NUMBER] some Init attributes was set to a bad number
    [NO_CLASS] @{i}class@{ui} not found
    [NO_MUI] a required MUI class not found
    [NO_MCC] a required MCC not found
    [NO_RXMEC] a required rxmec not found

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Objects creation" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectCreation"}

@EndNode

@Node "XNewObj" "RxMUI Functions - XNewObj"

  @{b}XNewObj@{ub} - Creates an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    name = XNewObj(className,objName,stem,freeChild)
    <class>,[name/O],[stem/V],[freeChild/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}

    Create an object of class @{i}class@{ui} named @{i}name@{ui} reading its
    attributes from @{i}stem@{ui}, if present, or @{i}name@{ui}.

    @{i}freeChild@{ui} makes XNewObj() destroy all the internal buffers
    and resets child stems.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    class - the class the object is istance of
    name - the name of the object
    stem - Init attribute are here, if present
    freeChild - reset children - default 1

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    name - the name of the object or an empty string on failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_MEM] not enough mem to complete the operation
    [BAD_VALUE] some Init attributes was set to a bad value
    [BAD_NUMBER] some Init attributes was set to a bad number
    [NO_CLASS] @{i}class@{ui} not found
    [NO_MUI] a required MUI class not found
    [NO_MCC] a required MCC not found
    [NO_RXMEC] a required rxmec not found

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Objects creation" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectCreation"}

@EndNode

@Node "Remove" "RxMUI Functions - Remove"

  @{b}Remove@{ub} - Removes an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = Remove(obj)
    <obj/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Remove @{i}obj@{ui} from its parent.

    The rules are:

    1. The object may refuse to be removed

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to remove

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [BUSY_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} is busy

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Objects creation" LINK "RxMUI.guide/ObjectCreation"}

@EndNode

@Node "Set" "RxMUI Functions - Set"

  @{b}Set@{ub} - Writes the value of an attribute of an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = set(obj,attr,value)
    <obj/V>,<attr/V>,<value>,[NoNotify/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}

    Sets ONE attribute of ONE object. SetAttr() is a synonymous
    for set().

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to set the attribute of
    attr - the S-attribute to set
    value - the value of the attribute
    NoNotify - an ARexx boolean that indicates to the function to
    perform a nnset rather that a set

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [BAD_NUMBER] bad integral number format
    [BAD_VALUE] the type of @{i}value@{ui} is not compatible with the type of @{i}attr@{ui}
    [BAD_SET_GET] the attributes can't be set for some reason

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    call set("win","open",1)

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MultiSetAttrs()" LINK "MultiSetAttrs"} @{"SetAttrs()" LINK "SetAttrs"} @{"SetClassAttrs()" LINK "SetClassAttrs"}

@EndNode

@Node "SetAttrs" "RxMUI Functions - SetAttrs"

  @{b}SetAttrs@{ub} - Sets many attributes of an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = SetAttrs(obj,stem)
    <obj/V>,<stem/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Sets many attributes of an object at once.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - the object to set the attributes of
    stem - an ARexx stem name

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [BAD_NUMBER] bad integral number format
    [BAD_VALUE] the type of a value is not compatible with the type of an attribute
    [BAD_SET_GET] the attributes can't be set for some reason

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    set.Disabled=1
    set.Contents="I am disabled"
    call SetAttrs("string","set")

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MultiSetAttrs()" LINK "MultiSetAttrs"} @{"set()" LINK "set"} @{"SetClassAttrs()" LINK "SetClassAttrs"}

@EndNode

@Node "SetClassAttrs" "RxMUI Functions - SetClassAttrs"

  @{b}SetClassAttrs@{ub} - Sets many foreign attributes of an object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = SetAttrs(class,obj,stem)
    <class/V>,<obj/V>,<stem/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Sets many attributes of the class @{i}class@{ui} of an object at once.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    class - the class the attributes to set belong to
    obj - the object to set the attributes of
    stem - an ARexx stem name

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_CLASS] @{i}class@{ui} not found
    [NO_OBJ] @{i}obj@{ui} not found
    [BAD_NUMBER] bad integral number format
    [BAD_VALUE] the type of a value is not compatible with the type of an attribute
    [BAD_SET_GET] the attributes can't be set for some reason

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    set.Value=0
    call SetAttrs("Slider","group","set")

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MultiSetAttrs()" LINK "MultiSetAttrs"} @{"set()" LINK "set"} @{"SetAttrs()" LINK "SetAttrs"}

@EndNode

@Node "MultiGetAttr" "RxMUI Functions - MultiGetAttr"

  @{b}MultiGetAttr@{ub} - Reads the values of an attribute of many objects.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = MultiGetAttr(stem)
    <stem/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Reads the values of an attribute of many objects at once.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - a stem name where to set the couple object/attribute
           in the field .N .n.attr and where the function will
           write the values in .N.value (n=0,...).

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] one object not found
    [BAD_SET_GET] one attribute can't be read for some reason

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    get.0="host";     get.0.attr="Contents"
    get.1="hostport"; get.1.attr="Integer"
    call MultiGetAttr("get")
    say get.0.value
    say get.1.value

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"GetAttr()" LINK "GetAttr"} @{"xget()" LINK "xget"}

@EndNode

@Node "MultiSetAttr" "RxMUI Functions - MultiSetAttr"

  @{b}MultiSetAttr@{ub} - Writes an attribute of many objects.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = MultiSetAttr(stem)
    <stem/V>,[NoNotify/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Writes an attribute of many objects at once.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - a stem name where to specify the
           object/attribute/value to set
    NoNotify - an ARexx boolean that indicates to the function to
               perform a nnset rather that a set

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    [NO_OBJ] one object not found
    [BAD_NUMBER] bad integral number format
    [BAD_VALUE] the type of a value is not compatible with the type of an attribute
    [BAD_SET_GET] one attribute can't be set for some reason

  @{b}Example@{ub}
    set.0="host"; set.0.attr="contents";set.0.value="www.amiga.org"
    set.1="hostport"; set.1.attr="integer"; set.1.value = 80
    call MultiSetAttr("set")

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"set()" LINK "set"} @{"SetAttrs()" LINK "SetAttrs"}

@EndNode

@Node "Button" "RxMUI Functions - Button"

  @{b}Button@{ub} - Creates a button.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = button(name,text)
    [name/O],[text];

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a button object named @{i}name@{ui} with @{i}text@{ui} as label.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the button
    text - the label of the button

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Text class" LINK "TextClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "ToggleButton" "RxMUI Functions - ToggleButton"

  @{b}ToggleButton@{ub} - Creates a toggle button.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = ToggleButton(name,text,selected)
    [name/O],[text],[selected/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a toggle button object named @{i}name@{ui} with @{i}text@{ui} as label
    in @{i}selected@{ui} state.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the button
    text - the label of the button
    selected - the state of the button

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Text class" LINK "TextClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "Checkmark" "RxMUI Functions - Checkmark"

  @{b}Checkmark@{ub} - Creates a checkmark.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = checkmark(name,selected)
    [name/O],[selected/N],[cchar]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a checkmark object named @{i}name@{ui} in @{i}selected@{ui} state.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the checkmark
    selected 0 the object is not selected, 1 the object is selected
    cchar - the control char for the object

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Image class" LINK "ImageClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "HBar" "RxMUI Functions - HBar"

  @{b}HBar@{ub} - Creates a HBar.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = HBar(pixels)
    [pixels/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a HBar object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    pixels - the width in pixels; if not supplied or 0, the bar
             will be horiz unlimited

  @{b}Result@{ub}
  oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of the
          object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "VBar" "RxMUI Functions - VBar"

  @{b}VBar@{ub} - Creates a VBar.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = VBar(pixels)
    [pixels/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a VBar object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    pixel - the height in pixels; if not supplied or 0, the bar
            will be vert unlimited

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "HSpace" "RxMUI Functions - HSpace"

  @{b}HSpace@{ub} - Creates a horiz space.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = HSpace(pixels)
    [pixels/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a horiz rectangle object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    pixels - the width in pixels; if not supplied or 0, the
             object will be horiz unlimited

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "HFSpace" "RxMUI Functions - HFSpace"

  @{b}HFSpace@{ub} - Creates a horiz space.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = HFSpace(string)
    [string]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a horiz rectangle object with a fixed width as the
    width of the given string.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    string - the rectangle width (default X)

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "VFSpace" "RxMUI Functions - VFSpace"

  @{b}VFSpace@{ub} - Creates a vert space.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = VFSpace(string)
    [string]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a vert rectangle object with a fixed height as the
    height of the given string.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    string - define the rectangle height (default A)

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "VSpace" "RxMUI Functions - VSpace"

  @{b}VSpace@{ub} - Creates a vert rectangle object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = VSpace(pixels)
    [pixels/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a vert rectangle object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    pixels - the height in pixels; if not supplied or 0, the
             object will be vert unlimited

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "HVSpace" "RxMUI Functions - HVSpace"

  @{b}HVSpace@{ub} - Creates a rectangle object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = HVSpace(hpixels,vpixels)
    [hpixels/N],[vpixels/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a rectangle object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    hpixels - the width in pixels; if not supplied or 0, the
               object will be horiz unlimited
    vpixels - the height in pixels; if not supplied or 0, the
              object will be vert unlimited

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "HWSpace" "RxMUI Functions - HWSpace"

  @{b}HWSpace@{ub} - Creates a rectangle object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = HWSpace(hpixels,vpixels)
    [weight/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a rectangle object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    width - the weight; default 100

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "VWSpace" "RxMUI Functions - VWSpace"

  @{b}VWSpace@{ub} - Creates a rectangle object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = VWSpace(hpixels,vpixels)
    [weight/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a rectangle object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    width - the vert weight; default 100

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object as an internal string

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Rectangle class" LINK "RectangleClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "MenuItem" "RxMUI Functions - MenuItem"

  @{b}MenuItem@{ub} - Create a menuitem

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = MenuItem(name,title,shortcut,checked,checkit,enabled)
    [name/O],[title],[shortcut],[flags],[exclude/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a Menuitem object. @{i}title@{ui} can be the special value
    "BAR" to create a bar. If no argument or just @{i}name@{ui} is
    supplied, a bar is created.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the object
    title - the title of the item
    shortcut - the shortcut for the item
    flags - One or more of:
       o CHECKED
       o CHECKIT
       o DISABLED
       o TOGGLE
    exclude - the mutual exclude mask

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Menuitem class" LINK "MenuClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "Label" "RxMUI Functions - Label"

  @{b}Label@{ub} - Creates a label.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = label(text,flags)
    <text>,[flags]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates un unnamed label object. The text is right aligned by
    default. The char _ may be used to underline a char.

    flags is one or more of:
    o Centered - the text is centered
    o Double - the object gets a phantom double frame
    o FreeHoriz - the object is horiz unlimited (otherwise it
      is limited by its text width)
    o FreeVert - the object is vert unlimited (otherwise it is
      limited by its text height)
    o Left - the text is left aligned

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    text - the text of the label
    flags - see above

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; an internal string on
            success

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Text class" LINK "TextClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "MakeObj" "RxMUI Functions - MakeObj"

  @{b}MakeObj@{ub} - Creates a MUI object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = MakeObj(name,type,parms)
    [name/O],[type],{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a MUI Object.

  Type can be one of:

   o @{fg shine}Balance@{fg text} - creates a Balance object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Balance")
     -

   o @{fg shine}BarTitle@{fg text} - creates a Bar with a title.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"BarTitle",text)
     [text]

   o @{fg shine}BetterBalance@{fg text} - creates a BetterBalance object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"BetterBalance",ObjectID)
     <ObjectID/N>

   o @{fg shine}Busy@{fg text} - creates a Busy object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Busy")
     -

   o @{fg shine}ColGroup@{fg text} - creates a columned Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"ColGroup",obj1,obj2,...)
     <cols/N>,<obj1>,{obj}

   o @{fg shine}Cycle@{fg text} - creates a Cycle object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Cycle",entries,key,active)
     <entries>,[key],[active/N]

   o @{fg shine}Gauge@{fg text} - creates a horiz Gauge object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Gauge",FixHeightTxt,max,current,InfoText)
     [FixHeightTxt],[max/N],[current/N],[InfoText]

   o @{fg shine}HBar@{fg text} - creates a horiz Bar.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HBar",pixels)
     [pixels/N]

   o @{fg shine}HCenter@{fg text} - center one object in a horiz Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HCenter",obj)
     <obj>

   o @{fg shine}HFrameGroup@{fg text} - incapsulate one object in a horiz framed
     Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HFrameGroup",title,obj,class)
     [title],<obj>,[class]

   o @{fg shine}HGroup@{fg text} - creates a horiz Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HGroup",obj)
     <obj1>,{obj}

   o @{fg shine}HLeft@{fg text} - incapsulate one object in a horiz Group with a
     hspace at the right.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HLeft",obj)
     <obj>

   o @{fg shine}HRight@{fg text} - incapsulate one object in a horiz Group with a
     hspace at the left.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HRight",obj)
     <obj>

   o @{fg shine}HSpace@{fg text} - creates a horiz Space.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"HSpace",pixels)
     [pixels/N]

   o @{fg shine}ImageButton@{fg text} - creates an Image button.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"ImageButton",ImgSpec,key,selected)
     [ImgSpec],[key],[selected/N]

   o @{fg shine}Knob@{fg text} - creates a Knob.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Knob",keymin,max,val,default)
     [key],[min/N],[max/N],[val/N],[default/N]

   o @{fg shine}Levelmeter@{fg text} - creates a Levelmeter.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Levelmeter",key,min,max,val,default)
     [key],[min/N],[max/N],[val/N],[label],[default/N]

   o @{fg shine}Menu@{fg text} - creates a Menu.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Menu",title,obj1,...)
     <title>,{obj}

   o @{fg shine}Menuitem@{fg text} - adds Menuitems to a Menuitem.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Menuitem",parent,child1,...)
     <parent>,{children}

   o @{fg shine}Menustrip@{fg text} - creates a Menu strip.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Menustrip",menu1,...)
     {menus}

   o @{fg shine}Numericbutton@{fg text} - creates a Numericbutton.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Numericbutton",key,min,max,val,format,default)
     [key],[min/N],[max/N],[val/N],[format],[default/N]

   o @{fg shine}NumericString@{fg text} - creates a numeric String.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"NumericString",key,min,max,MaxLen,val)
     [key],[min/N],[max/N],[MaxLen/N],[val/N]

   o @{fg shine}Radio@{fg text} - creates a Radio object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Radio",entries,key,active)
     <entries>,[key],[active/N]

   o @{fg shine}RowGroup@{fg text} - creates a rowed group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"RowGroup",rows,obj1,obj2,...)
     <rows/N>,<obj1>,{obj}

   o @{fg shine}Scale@{fg text} - creates a Scale object.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Scale")
     -

   o @{fg shine}Slider@{fg text} - creates a Slider.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"Slider",key,min,max,val,format,default)
     [key],[min/N],[max/N],[val/N],[format],[default/N]

   o @{fg shine}VBar@{fg text} - creates a vert Bar.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VBar",pixels)
     [pixels/N]

   o @{fg shine}VCenter@{fg text} - center one object in a vert Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VCenter",obj)
     <obj>

   o @{fg shine}VDown@{fg text} - incapsulate one object in a vert Group with a vspace
     at the bottom.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VDown",obj)
     <obj>

   o @{fg shine}VFrameGroup@{fg text} - incapsulate one object in a vert framed Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VFrameGroup",title,obj,class)
     [title],<obj>,[class]

   o @{fg shine}VGroup@{fg text} - creates a vert Group.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VGroup",obj1,...)
     <obj1>,{obj}

   o @{fg shine}VSpace@{fg text} - creates a vert Space.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VSpace",pixels)
     [pixels/N]

   o @{fg shine}VUp@{fg text} - incapsulate one object in a vert Group with a vspace
     at the top.
     oname = MakeObj(oname,"VUp",obj)
     <obj>

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the object
    type - the type of the object
    parms - parameters

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation same
    sub object creation failure; it may happens especially if:
    [NO_MUI] a required MUI class not found
    [NO_MCC] a required MCC not found
    [NO_RXMEC] a required rxmec not found

  @{b}Example@{ub}

    1. Imagebutton
       po.Button=MakeObj(,"Imagebutton","PopUp")

    2. Menustrip
       app.Menustrip=MakeObj(,"Menustrip",,
           MakeObj(,"Menu","Project",,
               Menuitem("mabout","About...","?"),,
               Menuitem("maboutrxmui","About RxMUI..."),,
               Menuitem("maboutmui","About MUI..."),,
               Menuitem("","BAR"),,
               Menuitem("mhide","Hide","H"),,
               Menuitem("","BAR"),,
               Menuitem("mquit","Quit","Q")),,
           MakeObj("medit","Menu","Editor",,
           MakeObj(,"Menuitem",Menuitem("mtest","Test"),,
               Menuitem("mtest1","Show all",,"CHECKED CHEKIT TOGGLE",6),,
               Menuitem("mtest2","Show left",,"CHEKIT TOGGLE",5),,
               Menuitem("mtest3","Show right",,"CHEKIT TOGGLE",3))))

    3. A complex group
       group = MakeObj(,"HFrameGroup","Numeric Buttons",,
           MakeObj(,"HCenter",,
           MakeObj(,"ColGroup",2,,
               Label("Low:"),,
               MakeObj(,"HGroup",,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%"),,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%"),,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%")),,
               Label("Mid:"),,
               MakeObj(,"HGroup",,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%"),,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%"),,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%")),,
               Label("High:"),,
               MakeObj(,"HGroup",,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%"),,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%"),,
                   MakeObj(,"NumericButton",,,,,"%ld %%")))))

@EndNode

@Node "String" "RxMUI Functions - String"

  @{b}String@{ub} - Creates a string.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = string(name,cchar,contents,max)
    [name/O],[cchar],[contents],[max/N]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a string object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the object
    cchar - the control char for the object
    content - the initial content
    max - max number of chars

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation
    [NO_MCC] a required MCC not found
    [NO_RXMEC] a required rxmec not found

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"String class" LINK "StringClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "Text" "RxMUI Functions - Text"

  @{b}Text@{ub} - Creates a text object.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    oname = text(name,text,frame,background,preparse)
    [name/O],[text],[frame],[background],[preparse]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Creates a text object.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    name - the name of the object
    text - the initial content of the object
    frame - the frame for the object - default TEXT
    background - the background for the object - default TEXTBACK
    preparse - the preparse for the object - default \\33c

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    oname - an empty string on failure; on success, the name of
            the object, as an internal string if @{i}name@{ui} was omitted
            or it was specified as an empty string, @{i}name@{ui} itself
            otherwise

  @{b}The function may fail if@{ub}
    there are not enough resources to complete the operation

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"Text class" LINK "TextClass.guide/Main"}

@EndNode

@Node "ParseText" "RxMUI Functions - ParseText"

  @{b}ParseText@{ub} - Parses text.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    parsedtext = ParseText(text)
    <text>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Parses a text, translating it to the MUI text engine format.

    Refer to the MUI text class autodoc.

    The changes made on @{i}text@{ui} are:
    o %c is changed to \\33c ("1B"x || c) (where c is ANY char)
    o \n is changed to "0A"x
    o \r is changed to "0D"x

    To display:
    o \\ use \\\\
    o % use \\%

    Without this function the strings to pass as Contents
    attribute of Text class, as Text argument in Button() or as
    entry of a List object would be too complicated.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    text - the text to parse

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    parsedText - the text parsed

@EndNode

@Node "StripText" "RxMUI Functions - StripText"

  @{b}StripText@{ub} - Strip dangerous codes from text.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    stripped = StripText(text)
    <text>

  @{b}Function@{ub}

    Anytime you are going to set a Contents of a Text object or
    you are adding an entry to a (N)List and so on, and the text
    comes from a non trustable source (e.g. from the Internet),
    you should strip dangerous MUI Text Engine codes via this
    function. It will return a clean text that may be used with
    no worries.

    Note that the function may not fail: if no mem is available
    it just returns an empty string.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    text - the text to strip

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    stripped - the text stripped

@EndNode

@Node "Child" "RxMUI Functions - Child"

  @{b}Child@{ub} - Defines a child.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    call child(parent,name,class)
    <parent/V>,<name/V>,[class/O]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    To use at object specification phase.
    call child("G","S","STRING")

    just tells RxMUI to:

    o init @{i}g@{ui}.0 to S - if it is the first time that child("G" ...)
      is used

    o init @{i}g@{ui}.i to S - if it the i-th time that child("G" ...) is
      used @{i}s@{ui}.class="STRING"

    A often used form is as in

    call child("MPROJECT",Menuitem("MOPEN","Open","O"))

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    parent - the container, parent of @{i}name@{ui}
    name - the name of the object, child of @{i}parent@{ui}
    class - the class of @{i}name@{ui}

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    none

  @{b}See@{b}
    @{"NewObj()" LINK "NewObj"}

@EndNode

@Node "MUIRequest" "RxMUI Functions - MUIRequest"

  @{b}MUIRequest@{ub} - Shows a requester.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = MUIRequest(app,win,title,gadgets,text)
    [app/O],[win/O],[title],[gadgets],[text]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Shows a MUI requester.

    This function is discouraged. Use it sparely, just to show
    errors and then exit.

    If you have to report messages to the user, you should better
    open a little window with a text (floattext) object and use
    it.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    app - the name of an application object
    win - the name of a window object that belongs to app
    title - the title of the requester
    gadgets - a string containing the text for the gadgets
              separated with a |
    text - the MUI text of the requester

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - the number of the gadget the user pressed to exit from
          the requester, with the usual requester-gadgets
          convection.

@EndNode

@Node "SetRxMUIStack" "RxMUI Functions - SetRxMUIStack"

  @{b}SetRxMUIStack@{ub} - Set RxMUI stack size.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    call SetRxMUIStack(size)
    <size/N>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Sets the RxMUI swap-stack size of the macro.

    Every RxMUI function is executed under a stack swap.

    Default stack size is 24k, but in certain situation with some
    object, e.g. with NListview, a very large stack is required.
    You can set the stack size with this function. RxMUI will
    allocate the new stack iff @{i}size@{ui} is >16k bytes. If the stack
    can not be allocated error 3 is generated.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    size - the new stack size

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    none

@EndNode

@Node "GetRxMUIString" "RxMUI Functions - GetRxMUIString"

  @{b}GetRxMUIString@{ub} - Returns an error string.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = GetRxMUIString(id)
    <id/N>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    The strings are read from the catalog rxmui.catalog if
    present.

    At this moment RxMUI errors code are:

    o @{fg shine}51 NO_MEM too few memory@{fg text}
      Not enough resources to perform the required operation,
      e.g. no mem or no Exec signal available.

    o @{fg shine}52 ARG_MISS required argument missed@{fg text}
      A required arguments was not supplied, e.g. attempt to
      create a Cycle object without defining the attribute
      Entries.

    o @{fg shine}53 BAD_NUMBER bad number@{fg text}
      The format of an integral number is not valid.

    o @{fg shine}54 BAD_VALUE bad value@{fg text}
      The value of an argument is not valid, or not in the range
      of the accepted values and so on.

    o @{fg shine}55 NO_CLASS can't find class@{fg text}
      Attempt to create an object of a class that can't be found.
      It might also mean that an external RxMUI class is missed.

    o @{fg shine}56 OBJ_EXISTS object already exists@{fg text}
      Not used.

    o @{fg shine}57 NO_OBJ can't find object@{fg text}
      An object can't be found.

    o @{fg shine}58 BUSY_OBJ object is busy@{fg text}
      An object is currently busy, e.g. attempt to add an object
      that was already added or attempt to use a Menustrip, used
      by an Application object as Menustrip, as Contextmenu of
      another object and so on.

    o @{fg shine}59 OBJ_CANT_BE_ADDED incompatible objects@{fg text}
      A couple of objects was interested in an operation but the
      objects are not compatible for that operation, e.g. attempt
      to add a Window object to a Group and so on.

    o @{fg shine}60 CANT_CREATE_OBJ object not created@{fg text}
      The object was not created for some reason.

    o @{fg shine}61 BAD_SET_GET bad attribute set or get@{fg text}
      The reading/setting attributes operation failed for some
      reason.

    o @{fg shine}62 OBJ_CANT_BE_DISPOSED object can't be disposed@{fg text}
      Attempt to dispose an object failed, because the object is
      in use somewhere, e.g. it is a Contextmenu or it is part of
      a Popstring object and so on.

    o @{fg shine}63 OBJ_CANT_BE_REMOVED object can't be removed@{fg text}
      Attempt to remove an object failed, because the object is
      in use somewhere, e.g. it is part of a Popstring object and
      so on.

    o @{fg shine}64 BAD_DANDD incompatible objects for D&D@{fg text}
      Attempt to set up an automatic Drag and Drop failed,
      because RxMUI doesn't know how to handle the Drag and Drop
      between the two objects.

    o @{fg shine}65 BAD_ATTRS incompatible attributes@{fg text}
      Attempt to set up a notification triggered by an attribute
      Everytime its value changes, invoking a method with a
      Triggervalue parameter that has a different type than the
      triggering attribute.

    o @{fg shine}66 NO_ATTR can't find attribute@{fg text}
      Attempt to perform an operation with an unknown attribute.

    o @{fg shine}67 ATTR_IS_NOT_S attribute is not settable@{fg text}
      Attempt to set an attribute that is not S.

    o @{fg shine}68 ATTR_IS_NOT_G attribute is not readable@{fg text}
      Attempt to read an attribute that is not G.

    o @{fg shine}69 ATTR_IS_NOT_N attribute is not notificated@{fg text}
      Attempt to set up a notification with a triggering
      attribute that is not N.

    o @{fg shine}70 NO_METHOD can't find method@{fg text}
      A method can't be found.

    o @{fg shine}71 METHOD_NOTIFY_ONLY the method can be notified only@{fg text}
      Attempt to directly use a notify-only method in DoMethod().

    o @{fg shine}72 METHOD_NONOTIFY the method can't be notified@{fg text}
      Attempt to set up a notification with a direct-only-method.

    o @{fg shine}73 BAD_NOTIFY can't add notify@{fg text}
      Attempt to set up a notification failed for some reason.

    o @{fg shine}74 BAD_TRIG_ATTR notify condition never true@{fg text}
      Attempt to set up a notification with a triggering
      condition that can't be never true, e.g. the trigger
      attribute has type S and the trigger value is Everytime.

    o @{fg shine}75 NO_MCC can't find MUI custom class@{fg text}
      Attempt to create an object of a class that is a subclass
      of a MUI Custom Class that can't be found. E.g. attempt to
      create a HTLMview object and HTMLview.mcc is not present in
      MUI:Libs/MUI drawer.

    o @{fg shine}76 NO_MUI can't find MUI class@{fg text}
      Attempt to create an object of a class that is a subclass
      of a MUI Class that can't be found. E.g. attempt to create
      a Knob object and Knob.mui is not present in MUI:Libs/MUI
      drawer.

    o @{fg shine}77 NO_RXMEC a required rxmec not found@{fg text}
      Attempt to create an object of a class that is a subclass
      of a RxMUI class, which can't be init or found. It might
      mean that a RxMUI external class is missed or that there
      are not enough resources to perform the operation.

    If an error is returned the var RxMUIErr is set to something
    meaningful, if possible.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    id - the id of the error string

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - the string associated with id

@EndNode

@Node "RxMUIOpt" "RxMUI Functions - RxMUIOpt"

  @{b}RxMUIOpt@{ub} - Sets or reads RxMUI options.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = RxMUIOpt(options)
    <options>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    @{i}options@{ui} is one or more of:

    o DebugMode - Default 1
    o ShowErr - Default 1

    When many objects are created via one single NewObj() call,
    if an object anywhere can not be created, all the created
    objects are disposed and NewObj() returns an error code.

    You have no way to know where the creation process stopped
    and the error was generated. During debugging of a macro is
    very useful to know exactly which object had problem and or
    where the problem appeared.

    Setting DebugMode makes RxMUI to remember the first error it
    discovered in NewObj().

    Setting ShowErr make RxMUI to show a MUI requester with info
    inside.

    @{i}options@{ui} may also be ASK in which case the string

    @{i}rxmui.library ver.rev (date) [user] DefStack GlobalStack@{ui}
    @{i}LocalStack DefMinStack GlobalMinStack LocalMinStack@{ui}
    @{i}DefDebugMode GlobalDebugMode LocalDebugMode DefShowErr@{ui}
    @{i}GlobalShowErr LocalShowErr@{ui}

    is returned.

    Note that everytime rxmui.library is load, it checks for the
    environment vars:

    o RxMUI/DebugMode
    o RxMUI/ShowErr

    You might change them to have personal global defaults.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    options - the options to set or "ASK"

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - 1 or an info string

@EndNode

@Node "RxMUIObjExists" "RxMUI Functions - RxMUIObjExists"

  @{b}RxMUIObjExists@{ub} - Checks if an object exists.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = RxMUIObjExists(obj)
    <obj/V>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Checks if @{i}obj@{ui} exists.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - an object name

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - An ARexx boolean

@EndNode

@Node "RxMUIObjList" "RxMUI Functions - RxMUIObjList"

  @{b}RxMUIObjList@{ub} - Returns the objects list.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = RxMUIObjList(obj)
    [obj/V]

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Returns an object list string. For debugging porpoise.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    obj - returns the list of the child of this object

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - The objects list.

@EndNode

@Node "RxMUIGetVar" "RxMUI Functions - RxMUIGetVar"

  @{b}RxMUIGetVar@{ub} - Gets a parent macro var.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    value = RxMUIGetVar(var)
    <var/S>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Many classes permit you to define a inline-macro function to
    be execute on some events. It is the case of
    Application/Inline method or Popstring/OpenFun attribute. In
    the macro you have no access to the vars of the parent macro,
    but you may still obtain the value of a var via this
    function.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    var - the var to read

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    value - the value of @{i}var@{ui}

  @{b}See@{ub}
    @{"RxMUISetVar()" LINK "RxMUISetVar"}

@EndNode

@Node "RxMUISetVar" "RxMUI Functions - RxMUISetVar"

  @{b}RxMUISetVar@{ub} - Sets a parent macro var.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    value = RxMUISetVar(var,value)
    <var/S>,<value>

  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Many classes permit you to define a inline-macro function to
    be execute on some events. It is the case of
    Application/Inline method or Popstring/OpenFun attribute. In
    the macro you have no access to the vars of the parent macro,
    but you may still set the value of a var via this function.

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    var - the var to set
    value - the value to set var to

  @{b}Result@{ub}
    value - @{i}value@{ui} itself

  @{b}See@{ub}
    @{"RxMUIGetVar()" LINK "RxMUIGetVar"}

@EndNode

